<font color="#FF0000">GIVE IT UP SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Wed Nov  5 19:24:32 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
See that's your problem, Spatz. Your preoccupation with being right. You had the audacity to demand a memorial in tribute of being right. Staying at home wasn't enough for you. You want to be rewarded.  <br><br>
You claim that Ed is egotistical, that we who contribute to this site are in need of pats on the back.  You are the one with the ego, the need to feel important. Remember your wild claim that you were the &quot;voice in our ears&quot; telling us not to go? It was very evident that you were striving for recognition. Instead, I told you that you were only kidding yourself if you actually thought you were the voice in ANYONES ears. Look it up on this site, spatz it is here. You admitted you were mistaken.<br><br>
In chess, we call that a wasted move. You retreated.<br><br>
My first post to you was an entreaty to all who thought there was a need for a &quot;rapprochement&quot; of the American people. That was the same post in which I accused you of being self righteous. Your subsequent post was an apology. Your apology was a ray of hope. I sincerely believed it.<br><br>
I didn't post much at first, until you referred to our combat decorations as being &quot;doggy treats&quot;. I asked you if you ever wondered what it was like to be a medic in combat, what it would be like to shit in your pants under fire. You stated that you didn't think you could have made it. I felt compassion for you. I know what being scared is like.<br><br>
You are here for your own recognition - under the guise of wanting to explain all the various sides of the Vietnam War. <br>
If you actually understood or had the propensity to WANT to understand, you would recognize the profound, healing effects of what you call &quot;Indian mumbo jumbo&quot;. Go back and read the words of Captain Edward Ramon (and the others you have insulted) in the Inner Circle thread. You won't do it, because there is nothing there that you want to hear.<br><br>
You were caught in a lie, yet you claim that none here want to face the truth that you can provide. Is it truth that you seek, or is it recognition that you want? It can't be truth, because you fabricated a lie about lying in front of a train.<br><br>
In chess, that would be the equivalent of losing your queen. A disaster! Typical of those who fail to understand, you don't know when to give up the game!<br><br>
I would love to take you up on the offer you made in your last paragraph, but you no longer have me convinced that you really are or were a war resistor.<br><br>
Give it up.
